e and allows for outstanding and compassionate patient care in a highly supervised setting our research involvement is extensive our division engages in many clinical trials attempting to address important and unanswered questions we have studies that cover a broad range of obstetrical care issues and encourage our patients to participate in these studies if they are so inclined in short we offer the very best in high risk obstetrical care in a safe and compassionate setting we welcome you as a patient you are here stanford medicine school of medicine departments obstetrics & gynecology obgyn divisions centers & programs maternal fetal medicine navigation for this section obstetrics & gynecology home education research patient care community divisions centers & programs faculty contact us additional links clinical divisions gynecologic specialties gynecologic oncology maternal fetal medicine overview faculty & staff fellowships mothers and newborns class reproductive endocrinology & infertility additional links programs reproductive biology and stem cell research women's health additinal links centers charles b and ann l johnson center for pregnancy and newborn services additinal links consortiums cooperative ovarian cancer group cogi site navigation home education overview residency fellowship clerkship research overview clinical trials patient care overview clinical trials community overview divisions centers & programs overview divisions gynecologic specialties gynecologic oncology maternal fetal medicine reproductive endocrinology & infertilit programs reproductive biology and stem cell research women's health centers charles b and ann l johnson center for pregnancy and newborn services consortiums cooperative ovarian cancer group cogi faculty department faculty contact us department contacts direction stanford medicine resources stanford medicine getting care overview find a physician find a clinical care center stanford hospital & clinics lucile packard childr